[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man's body found after St Leonards house fire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man's body has been found following a fire at a house.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The blaze, which broke at an address in West Hill Road, St Leonards,  just after 17:30 GMT on Thursday, is being treated as unexplained.
The body of a man, believed to be in his 70s, was found inside the house. Sussex Police said the coroner had been informed.
Detective Inspector Andy Eggleton said the investigation was in its early stages and appealed for witnesses.
